@The\_Earth\_dragon  
Strange you should make that argument on the one titan that is the most fun to play with and watch. The only titan that is incredibly above the curve is Primeval Titan, because of his ability to grab any two land, an ability surely worth 6 mana by itself, which often leads to the game being won immediately afterwards. For the others, you get a 3ish cmc spell thrown on for whenever your fatty comes into play or attacks. Quite powerful, but not "No fun to play with or against." Have you ever slapped a [Basilisk collar](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Basilisk collar) on an [Inferno Titan](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Inferno Titan) and laughed like a madman while you smash them in the face for a bajillion lifelink and gatling down his creatures? No? Have you recurred your [Lightning Greaves](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Lightning Greaves) with Sunny here, smashed for six, and ripped a [Tectonic Edge](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Tectonic Edge) out to smash into your opponent's [Cabal Coffers](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Cabal Coffers)?  
Sure, Sun Titan and Primeval Titan, and to a lesser extent, Grave... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)
